When I prepared this dish, the skin on the hens burnt. Too much sugar? It sounded great, but was disappointed. Any suggestions gladly accepted.

Rating: 3
This had a nice flavor (made with Soy Vay Veri Veri Teriyaki and fresh-squeezed OJ), but adding the chicken broth to the sauce was a mistake. There was plenty of sauce without it, and the chicken broth just made it too thin. I ended up using cornstarch to thicken it a bit. Next time, no broth.